This topic describes how to install and configure ECS Service Broker for Pivotal Cloud Foundry (PCF).

##<a id='install'></a> Install and Configure ECS Service Broker for PCF

1. Download the product file from [Pivotal Network](https://network.pivotal.io/products/ecs-cf-broker).

2. Navigate to the Ops Manager Installation Dashboard and click **Import a Product** to upload the product file.

3. Under the **Import a Product** button, click **+** next to the version number of ECS Service Broker for PCF.
This adds the tile to your staging area.

4. Click the newly added **ECS Service Broker for PCF** tile.

##<a id='install'></a>Configure ECS Service Broker for PCF

1. Click **Service Broker Application**.
2. For **Service Broker Application Name**, enter the name for the service broker app.
3. For **Service Broker Application version**, enter the version of the service broker app.
   (Final app name will include an app version like `${appName}-${appversion}`.
4. For **Service Broker Application URI**, enter the URI/endpoint for the service broker app (on push to CF).
5. For **Open up Security Groups**, check to open up security group on CF for service broker to access other apps or CF Cloud Controller.
6. For **Enable Global access to all Services and Plans**, check to open up access to all service plans across all orgs and spaces.
7. For **ECS Management Endpoint**, enter the URI/endpoint for the ECS HTTPS management API.
8. For **ECS Object Endpoint**, Enter the URI/endpoint for the ECS S3 API. Not needed the base URL endpoint should be used.
9. (Optional) For **ECS Base URL**, enter the name of the ECS configured base URL that should be used with bucket credentials.
10. (Optional) For **Repository Endpoint**, enter the URI/endpoint for the ECS S3 API that should be used for persisting broker metadata.
    Defaults to the object endpoint or base URL.
11. For **Replication Group**, enter the ID of the ECS replication group to be used for created buckets.
12. For **Namespace**, enter the name of the ECS namespace to be used for created buckets and users.
13. (Optional) For **Repository User**, enter the name of the user that should be created/used for managing broker metadata.
14. (Optional) For **Repository Bucket**, enter the name of the bucket that should be created/used for managing broker metadata.
15. For **ECS Admin Username**, enter the name of the ECS Management API user.
16. For **ECS Admin Password**, enter the ECS Management API password.
17. (Optional) For **ECS Repository Prefix**, enter a string used to prefix broker created buckets and users.
18. For **ECS Management Certification**, enter certification to enable the broker to communicate with ECS API Managment.
19. For **ECS Broker Security Username**, enter the name for the register broker.
    Defaults to "user".
20. For **ECS Broker Password**, enter the password for the register broker.
    Defaults to "password".
21. For **ECS Management API Version**, enter the ECS management API version.
22. Click **Save**.
23. Return to the Ops Manager Installation Dashboard and click **Apply Changes** to install ECS Service Broker for PCF.
